Some members of the APC National Executive Committee under the aegis of NON-NWC (NEC) Forum have requested for an urgent meeting with the party’s National Working Committee (NWC) led by Comrade Adams Oshiomhole. In a letter addressed to Oshiomhole dated May 29, they said the meeting was necessary to address critical issues affecting the ruling party. The letter jointly signed by Alh. Nasiru Danu and Hon. Omolaoye O. Akintola, forum’s chairman and secretary respectively, said the meeting was delayed till after the polls because they considered the concluded 2019 general elections as determinant of the party’s survival. The letter titled was ‘Demand for an Urgent Interface with NWC Organ of our Party – APC. We will resist attempts aimed at disrupting peace in APC - Spokesman APC state chairmen back govs on indirect primaries NWC abandons PDP secretariat as BoT, NEC back aggrieved workers Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin